radiographic_examinations.findings: Bibasilar dependent atelectasis; spleen, adrenals, pancreas, gallbladder, liver, and kidneys appear normal; no free air or fluid; normal bowel; no transit of oral contrast into the cecum; 7 mm normal appendix; small amount of simple fluid near the cecal base; trace fluid in the cul-de-sac; normal uterus and adnexa; normal bladder; no adenopathy; no suspicious sclerotic or lytic lesions.
